A Lagos Federal High Court on Monday ordered the forfeiture of two houses belonging to the immediate past Senate President, Bukola Saraki. The houses are located at plots 10 and 11 Abdulkadir Road, GRA, Ilorin, Kwara State. Justice Rilwan Aikawa gave the order following an application filed by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC. Details Later… Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.